From: burakgon <burakgon12@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: Intel: sof_sdw: Add SOC_SDW_SIDECAR_AMPS quirk for ASUS ExpertBook Ultra B9406CAA

The 2026 ASUS ExpertBook Ultra B9406CAA (Panther Lake, PCI subsystem
0x1043:0x15e4) has a CS42L43 codec on SoundWire link 3 and two CS35L56
sidecar speaker amplifiers on SoundWire link 2. The SOF topology
sof-ptl-cs42l43-agg-l3-cs35l56-l2.tplg loads correctly, but without a
quirk entry the sof_sdw machine driver does not flag the sidecar amps,
so ALSA UCM cannot match the resulting card to a HiFi profile and
WirePlumber falls back to "stereo-fallback" which never reaches the
cs35l56 output path. End-user symptom: speakers silent through PipeWire
even when direct ALSA playback to plughw:0,2 produces sound.

Mirror the existing Lenovo 0x3821 entry — same SOC_SDW_SIDECAR_AMPS flag
applied via PCI subsystem ID matching in sof_sdw_ssid_quirk_table.
Other ASUS systems already in this table (Zenbook S14/S16) use
SOC_SDW_CODEC_MIC because they have no sidecar amps; ours is
structurally closer to the Lenovo P1/P16 + Dell PTL/CS42L43 systems
that combine cs42l43 with cs35l56 amps.

Tested on:
  - ASUS ExpertBook Ultra B9406CAA (Panther Lake)
  - Linux 7.x with the per-OEM firmware
    cs35l56-b0-dsp1-misc-104315e4-l2u{0,1}.{wmfw,bin} in /lib/firmware

Signed-off-by: burakgon <burakgon12@gmail.com>
---
 sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c b/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
--- a/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
+++ b/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
@@ -844,6 +844,7 @@ static const struct snd_pci_quirk sof_sdw_ssid_quirk_table[] = {
 	SND_PCI_QUIRK(0x1043, 0x1e13, "ASUS Zenbook S14", SOC_SDW_CODEC_MIC),
 	SND_PCI_QUIRK(0x1043, 0x1f43, "ASUS Zenbook S16", SOC_SDW_CODEC_MIC),
+	SND_PCI_QUIRK(0x1043, 0x15e4, "ASUS ExpertBook Ultra B9406CAA", SOC_SDW_SIDECAR_AMPS),
 	SND_PCI_QUIRK(0x17aa, 0x2347, "Lenovo P16", SOC_SDW_CODEC_MIC),
 	SND_PCI_QUIRK(0x17aa, 0x2348, "Lenovo P16", SOC_SDW_CODEC_MIC),
 	SND_PCI_QUIRK(0x17aa, 0x2349, "Lenovo P1", SOC_SDW_CODEC_MIC),
